[ chuckles ]
I'm serious.

07:21.520 --> 07:24.865
I used to think
that tall white hat
was cool as hell.

07:24.920 --> 07:27.218
- And that jacket?
Come on, now.
- The jacket?

07:27.270 --> 07:29.613
[laughs]
You know what?

07:29.660 --> 07:32.447
- I should pick that up again.
- [ sighs ]

07:32.490 --> 07:35.004
As a hobby.

07:35.060 --> 07:37.221
- You're serious?
- I'm serious.

07:37.280 --> 07:41.364
Like you're not
enough things right now.

07:41.410 --> 07:44.971
Let's see-- professor,
irrigation specialist.

07:45.020 --> 07:48.717
- Yeah.
- Seed developer,
cowboy hat wearer.

07:48.770 --> 07:51.113
- Oh, jokes.
- I'm just--

07:51.160 --> 07:54.459
- She thinks she's got jokes.
- I mean, you wear
a cowboy hat.

07:54.510 --> 07:57.297
[ both laughing ]

07:57.340 --> 07:59.126
This is nice.

07:59.170 --> 08:02.958
- What, being out together?
- Yeah.

08:03.000 --> 08:04.729
Being out together.

08:04.780 --> 08:07.431
- [ music playing ]
- [ chatter ]

08:18.490 --> 08:21.448
- Thank you for dinner.
- Thank you.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.798
- [ phone ringing ]
- Oh.

08:28.070 --> 08:30.538
- My mother.
Two seconds?
- Okay.

08:31.640 --> 08:33.062
Hi, Mother.

08:35.950 --> 08:37.986
Okay, right.

08:39.120 --> 08:41.771
Right.

08:41.820 --> 08:45.256
Okay, let me just get home
and-- and we can make a plan.

08:46.390 --> 08:49.120
What?

08:49.180 --> 08:51.045
In Louisiana?

08:53.310 --> 08:56.962
Yeah. No, no.
Yes, I-- I understand.

09:01.270 --> 09:02.885
What's up?

09:05.370 --> 09:06.974
My mother.

09:08.980 --> 09:10.584
She's here.

09:13.110 --> 09:15.192
Hollywood:
All right, y'all,
y'all boys work fast.

09:15.250 --> 09:17.377
Got lunch in 30 minutes,
we'll be done with this
about 10:00.

09:17.420 --> 09:19.411
So, you go ahead
and you grab that.
Take that one.

09:19.470 --> 09:21.461
- Go take it back there
to the back, all right?
- Okay.

09:21.510 --> 09:23.421
[ continues indistinctly ]

09:26.560 --> 09:28.994
Hey, uh, foreman told me
to find you, Mr. Desonier.

09:29.040 --> 09:31.167
Name's Will Roseman.
I think I'm joining your team.

09:31.220 --> 09:32.869
Oh, hey.
Just call me Hollywood.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.524
You ever driven
piles before?

09:34.570 --> 09:36.219
No, I worked
on the Columba Driller

09:36.270 --> 09:38.044
as a tool pusher before
the bastards at the company

09:38.090 --> 09:39.614
laid me off
three months ago.

09:39.660 --> 09:40.911
You know,
I used to be a driller

09:40.970 --> 09:43.131
on the Octa Oleum
in Vermilion Bay.

09:43.190 --> 09:44.316
- No shit?
- Yeah.

09:44.360 --> 09:45.702
It's nice working
with somebody

09:45.750 --> 09:47.627
that knows what it's like
to be stepped on.

09:47.670 --> 09:49.706
I hear you, brother.

09:49.760 --> 09:52.058
Look here,
those guys are unloading
the rest of the equipment.

09:52.110 --> 09:54.499
- They could use
a couple of hands.
- You got it.

10:00.460 --> 10:02.416
- [ music playing ]
- [ chatter ]

10:22.920 --> 10:24.353
Charley:
Hello, Mother.

10:25.710 --> 10:29.669
You look incredible,
as always.

10:29.710 --> 10:32.406
Oh.
[laughs]

10:32.450 --> 10:35.795
And you... look healthy,

10:35.850 --> 10:39.286
which is saying a lot
considering all you have
been through.

10:39.330 --> 10:40.638
Good for you.

10:40.680 --> 10:41.977
It's not easy to hold
yourself together

10:42.030 --> 10:44.851
during tough times.

10:44.900 --> 10:46.458
[ sighs ]

10:48.950 --> 10:50.986
Charlotte...

10:51.040 --> 10:54.908
listen, I really do wish
that I could've gotten

10:54.950 --> 10:59.171
off that boat sooner,
but I was Lauren's guest.

10:59.220 --> 11:01.688
And, I don't know,
with her husband

11:01.740 --> 11:03.696
having just left her,
it really felt like

11:03.750 --> 11:05.741
being there for her
was the right thing to do

11:05.790 --> 11:08.520
just as a friend, and...

11:08.580 --> 11:11.048
and, honestly,
I think I needed
that cruise myself.

11:11.100 --> 11:14.399
I mean, I just needed it
to process your father,
because...

11:17.240 --> 11:19.049
it, uh--

11:19.110 --> 11:21.499
it hit me harder
than I expected.

11:24.850 --> 11:26.806
So, being out there
on the water

11:26.860 --> 11:28.987
and on the other side
of the world,

11:29.030 --> 11:32.204
that was really
a blessing for me.

11:32.250 --> 11:37.119
And that's
a long way of saying
that I really...

11:37.170 --> 11:40.731
do wish that I--
I could've come and
checked on you sooner.

11:40.780 --> 11:45.695
And I'm sorry that I didn't,
but I was-- just wasn't able.

11:49.360 --> 11:51.749
No apology necessary, Mom.

11:51.790 --> 11:53.394
Really, I understand.

11:53.450 --> 11:54.963
Thank you.

11:56.840 --> 11:58.319
Micah:
Grandma.

11:58.360 --> 11:59.668
Micah?

11:59.710 --> 12:02.759
Oh, honey.
Oh!

12:02.800 --> 12:05.234
Gosh. Tsk.

12:05.280 --> 12:07.669
Oh, look how much
you've grown.

12:07.720 --> 12:09.062
- Micah: Yeah.
- Oh, my gosh,
I've missed you.

12:09.110 --> 12:11.192
Micah:
Yeah, I missed you, too.

12:11.250 --> 12:12.854
Chantal:
Zika, Nova?

12:12.900 --> 12:14.458
You've been writing
about criminal justice

12:14.510 --> 12:16.466
and mass incarceration,
but now all of a sudden

12:16.510 --> 12:18.330
you're an expert
in this disease?

12:18.380 --> 12:19.813
I've done enough research
to know it's naive

12:19.860 --> 12:21.680
to ignore the fact
that the economic havoc

12:21.740 --> 12:23.992
in our community
doesn't just keep
black people behind bars.

12:24.040 --> 12:26.736
It also puts
the most vulnerable of us

12:26.780 --> 12:28.782
at the greatest risk
of contracting this virus.

12:28.830 --> 12:30.309
No, you don't get it.

12:30.350 --> 12:32.136
People are coming in,
and they're scared.

12:32.180 --> 12:33.488
They don't know
where to turn.

12:33.530 --> 12:35.179
I understand,
they're concerned.

12:35.230 --> 12:38.529
"They're concerned"?
Nova, they are freaking out!

12:38.580 --> 12:40.400
You know what?

12:40.450 --> 12:44.841
I feel like
this is just about
being provocative.

12:44.890 --> 12:46.881
Like you're trying
to scare white folk

12:46.940 --> 12:49.545
into some kind of action.

12:49.590 --> 12:52.286
Hey, there.
Everything okay?

12:52.330 --> 12:54.890
Nova:
Robert, this is Chantal.

12:54.940 --> 12:56.669
She's with
the Health Collective.

12:56.730 --> 12:59.858
- Ah, pleasure to meet you.
- I know who you are.

12:59.900 --> 13:03.199
The number of Zika cases
in New Orleans is negligible.

13:03.260 --> 13:05.125
Not one _ _
from local transmISSIon.

13:05.170 --> 13:06.728
And you think
there won't be?

13:06.780 --> 13:08.600
I'm trying to understand
what it is

13:08.650 --> 13:10.789
you believe in
these days, Nova.

13:10.830 --> 13:12.525
[ scoffs ]

13:25.840 --> 13:28.661
Robert:
What you're doing--
the second-guessing,

13:28.720 --> 13:30.756
it's not helpful.

13:30.810 --> 13:33.620
Maybe I should've
dialed back the rhetoric.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.068
It's not how I work.

13:42.950 --> 13:45.908
Is this about my role?

13:45.950 --> 13:48.077
Look, I'd be lying
ifI said that

13:48.130 --> 13:49.734
