Both:
And ever, and ever,
and ever, and ever.

17:01.450 --> 17:03.532
- [ laughs ] And ever.
- Right.

17:03.580 --> 17:05.445
Ever, ever, ever!

17:08.670 --> 17:09.841
[ music playing ]

17:09.890 --> 17:12.029
[vocalizing ]

17:15.860 --> 17:18.545
- Come to your river
- Wash my soul

17:18.600 --> 17:21.728
- I will come
to your river
- Wash my soul

17:21.770 --> 17:24.295
I will come
to your river

17:24.340 --> 17:28.219
Wash my soul again

17:28.260 --> 17:31.047
Carry away
my dead leaves

17:31.090 --> 17:34.082
- Let me
baptize my soul...
- [ watch beeps ]

17:34.140 --> 17:36.267
You redecorating?

17:36.310 --> 17:40.519
Chantal's arranging a Q&A
for folks scared about Zika.

17:40.580 --> 17:41.968
I'm gonna help out,

17:42.010 --> 17:44.444
connect with the community
in a tangible way.

17:44.490 --> 17:47.402
And you sure
she doesn't have
some agenda?

17:48.800 --> 17:50.756
[ doorbell rings ]

17:57.420 --> 17:59.854
Blue!
I haven't seen you
in a minute.

17:59.900 --> 18:02.334
- What you been up to?
- I have a school project.

18:02.380 --> 18:05.247
- I'm making a family tree.
- Ralph Angel: That's what
brings us by.

18:05.300 --> 18:09.122
Blue wanted
to find out if you got
any pictures of Mama.

18:09.170 --> 18:10.944
- This is my brother,
Ralph Angel.
- What's up, man?

18:11.000 --> 18:12.729
- Nice to meet you.
- His son, Blue.

18:12.780 --> 18:15.829
This is Robert.
He just stopped by
while he was out for a run.

18:15.870 --> 18:17.861
- Nice to meet you guys.
- Nice to meet you, man.

18:17.920 --> 18:19.820
- I'll catch you later?
- Yeah.

18:24.750 --> 18:26.138
She has big hair.

18:26.190 --> 18:28.146
[ chuckles ]
That's called a natural.

18:28.190 --> 18:30.704
She looks like you,
Auntie Nova.

18:30.760 --> 18:33.228
Carry away
my old leaves

18:33.280 --> 18:34.884
Let me baptize
my soul...

18:34.930 --> 18:37.364
[ sighs ]
She does, don't she?

18:37.420 --> 18:39.718
Sink my pains
and complains

18:39.770 --> 18:41.715
Let the river
take them

18:41.770 --> 18:42.987
River drown them...

18:43.030 --> 18:44.725
I appreciate this, Nova.

18:44.770 --> 18:46.158
Of course.

18:46.210 --> 18:49.247
Oh, and, Auntie Nova,

18:49.300 --> 18:52.428
Mama and Pop
are getting married.

18:54.130 --> 18:57.429
Talk about
burying the lede.

18:57.480 --> 18:58.515
Is it true?

18:59.610 --> 19:00.861
He ain't lying.

19:00.920 --> 19:03.878
[ chuckles ]
Got a big mouth, though.

19:03.920 --> 19:05.137
But it's true.

19:05.180 --> 19:07.398
I'm happy for you, Rah.

19:07.450 --> 19:10.317
- And Darla, too.
- Appreciate that, sis.

19:10.360 --> 19:12.828
[laughs]

19:12.890 --> 19:15.051
Ralph Angel:
Big mouth.

19:15.110 --> 19:17.499
I mean, I had
considered mauve,

19:17.540 --> 19:21.624
but I just feel like gray
was a better compliment,
and...

19:21.680 --> 19:26.856
Well, it's, uh,
a bit industrial,
isn't it?

19:26.900 --> 19:28.674
- [ sighs ]
- So?

19:28.730 --> 19:31.073
Lofts are in.

19:31.120 --> 19:34.203
Well, I just mean
it doesn't feel homey,
that's all I'm saying.

19:34.260 --> 19:36.251
And remember,
you are competing
with Davis now.

19:36.300 --> 19:39.827
I am not competing
with Davis.

19:39.870 --> 19:42.122
Yes, you are, honey.

19:42.180 --> 19:44.262
Even if you don't
think you are.

19:44.310 --> 19:46.824
And which house
do you think that Micah

19:46.880 --> 19:49.041
will be _
more comfortable in?

19:51.530 --> 19:52.929
Micah likes it here.

19:54.750 --> 19:56.968
So do I.

19:57.020 --> 20:00.399
This place, uh,
connects him...

20:00.460 --> 20:02.530
well, both of us
to our history.

20:04.370 --> 20:06.895
Sugarcane
was a big part of that.

20:14.820 --> 20:17.459
Your hair
is so beautiful.

20:17.520 --> 20:19.988
I didn't think
you'd like it.

20:20.040 --> 20:21.257
I do.

20:23.480 --> 20:26.608
_ But there are
just so many changes,
and all at once.

20:26.660 --> 20:29.606
Your hair and your clothes
and the way you live.

20:29.660 --> 20:33.391
Every step of this
has been my choice.

20:33.440 --> 20:35.317
Choice or reaction?

20:35.360 --> 20:40.536
- I understand divorce.
- Mom... I'm happy.

20:49.330 --> 20:51.582
Well,
if you're determined
to stay here,

20:51.640 --> 20:54.370
then at least let me
whip these barracks
into shape.

20:56.730 --> 20:59.813
And you need
a new rug immediately.

20:59.860 --> 21:02.328
Food storage
clearly labelled.

21:02.390 --> 21:04.904
Your surfaces
are all spotless.

21:04.950 --> 21:07.771
You even got
the meat thermometers
calibrated.

21:07.830 --> 21:09.991
You really turned
this place around.

21:10.050 --> 21:11.438
It's what I do.

21:11.480 --> 21:13.869
Now, I'm gonna send
you home some pies.

21:13.920 --> 21:16.559
- Oh, well,
thank you, ma'am.
-[laughs]

21:16.620 --> 21:19.999
_ All I need
is your Signature
here, here, here,

21:20.060 --> 21:21.482
and then just initials
on the second page.

21:21.540 --> 21:24.179
Okay, I gotcha.

21:27.060 --> 21:30.018
- You all right?
- I'm fine, baby.

21:30.070 --> 21:33.369
Um, show me where
to sign again, please?

21:36.730 --> 21:38.504
Good work today,
gentlemen.

21:38.550 --> 21:40.074
Hey, Hollywood,
you never did say

21:40.120 --> 21:43.203
why they laid you off
from your rig.

21:43.250 --> 21:46.071
Well, they didn't.

21:46.130 --> 21:48.428
I broke the contract
with the company.

21:48.480 --> 21:50.038
Decided I'd rather
spend my time

21:50.090 --> 21:51.864
_ closer to home
With my lady, Violet.

21:53.960 --> 21:55.086
Must be nice.

21:56.880 --> 21:59.747
Thought I'd catch y'all
before you were gone.

21:59.790 --> 22:01.132
Turns out we're gonna
have more work

22:01.180 --> 22:02.920
than we know what
to do with for a while,

22:02.970 --> 22:04.961
so I'm authorized
to make formal offers

22:05.010 --> 22:06.659
for you men to stay on
permanently.

22:06.710 --> 22:08.018
Hell, yeah.

22:08.060 --> 22:10.233
Hollywood, we sure
would like for you

22:10.280 --> 22:11.326
to keep
running your crew.

22:11.370 --> 22:12.496
What do you say?

22:14.460 --> 22:16.542
Why don't you give me
a little time to think
on that, okay?

22:26.600 --> 22:28.943
- [ keyboard clacking ]
- What are you working on?

22:28.990 --> 22:32.255
I'm writing a paper
on the Dred Scott
v. Sandford case.

22:32.300 --> 22:35.212
Oh. 1857.

22:35.260 --> 22:38.172
"A negro whose ancestors
were imported

22:38.220 --> 22:40.563
into this country
and sold as slaves,

22:40.620 --> 22:43.487
whether enslaved or free,

22:43.530 --> 22:46.488
could not be
an American Citizen."

22:46.530 --> 22:49.351
- You wanna write it for me?
- No, I do not. [ laughs ]

22:51.230 --> 22:53.232
I'm proud of you, man.

22:53.280 --> 22:55.589
- Yep.
- Yeah, I am.

22:55.630 --> 22:57.359
[ keyboard clacking ]

23:03.510 --> 23:04.932
Micah, listen, um...

23:08.990 --> 23:11.902
I've been wanting to talk
to you about that night.

23:11.950 --> 23:13.736
- [ sighs ] Dad, please.
- Micah, listen, listen.

23:13.780 --> 23:16.385
Hey, we have
to tell your mother.

23:16.430 --> 23:17.567
- No.
- Yes.

23:17.610 --> 23:18.861
- We don't.
- Yes, we do.

23:18.910 --> 23:20.559
Micah, we can't keep it
from her, man.

23:20.610 --> 23:23.738
- Come on.
- She doesn't want
to hear about it.

23:23.790 --> 23:25.519
All she wants to hear about
is the good things--

23:25.570 --> 23:28.482
the "A" on the paper,
not...

23:28.530 --> 23:30.703
Micah, you gotta
give your mother

23:30.750 --> 23:32.445
a little more credit
than that, okay?

23:32.490 --> 23:36.403
- She stands by her family.
- Is that why she left you?

23:37.590 --> 23:38.887
She left everything.

23:38.930 --> 23:41.455
She brought me
down here, like...

23:41.500 --> 23:42.888
Yeah, but look, man,

23:42.940 --> 23:44.805
divorce is hard
on everybody.

23:47.070 --> 23:50.688
And your mother,
she, um...

23:50.730 --> 23:52.243
she did stand by me.

23:56.340 --> 23:58.422
But what I put her through
was beyond difficult,

23:58.480 --> 24:00.778
and--
[ clears throat ]

24:00.830 --> 24:02.775
I'm not sure another woman
would've stood by me

24:02.830 --> 24:04.479
the way she did, so.

24:10.660 --> 24:12.833
Listen,

24:12.880 --> 24:17.533
being a parent is not
just about the good stuff.

24:17.580 --> 24:20.140
It's also about
the harder stuff.

24:20.190 --> 24:23.887
And thatis something
your mother understands.

24:27.500 --> 24:29.764
Lorna:
How many people
do you employ here?

24:29.810 --> 24:31.459
Charley:
About 100.

24:31.510 --> 24:33.671
Wow, well, I like
the sound of that.

24:33.730 --> 24:35.550
But, honestly,
is this really

24:35.600 --> 24:37.500
the best use
for your degree?

24:37.560 --> 24:39.118
Charley:
Well, I'm running
a business,

24:39.170 --> 24:41.775
exactly what
an MBA is for.

24:41.820 --> 24:44.516
Yes, but you were
so happy doing what
you were doing,

24:44.570 --> 24:47.949
negoﬁaﬂng
his million-dollar contracts,
his endorsement deals.

24:48.000 --> 24:49.524
That seemed like
a much better ﬁt

24:49.570 --> 24:53.438
than boilers, cranes,
vacuum pans.

24:53.490 --> 24:55.481
I'm not married
to DaVIS anymore,

24:55.530 --> 24:57.748
if you haven't noticed.

24:57.800 --> 25:00.052
But please,
any professional athlete

25:00.100 --> 25:03.319
- would be lucky to have you
as their manager.
- Mom.

25:03.370 --> 25:07.363
I'm the first black woman
to own a mill in this state.

25:07.410 --> 25:08.843
That's not small-scale.

25:08.890 --> 25:13.543
My question is will you
be satisfied with this?

25:13.590 --> 25:15.854
Remy:
Let's just make sure
this thing's chopped up,

25:15.900 --> 25:18.858
because if it gets locked down,
we're gonna be in trouble.

25:23.340 --> 25:25.160
[ coughs ]

25:25.210 --> 25:29.032
Lorna Prescott,
meet Remy Newell.

25:29.090 --> 25:32.309
Remy,
this is my mother.

25:32.350 --> 25:34.045
A pleasure to meet you,
Ms. Prescott.

25:34.090 --> 25:36.399
You raised one hell
of a daughter here.

25:36.440 --> 25:38.658
Well, tell me,
Mr. Newell,

25:38.710 --> 25:40.098
what is it
that you do here?

25:40.140 --> 25:43.576
Well, I've, uh,
engineered the seed cane

25:43.620 --> 25:47.317
that is the basis
for the current
Bordelon crop

25:47.370 --> 25:51.010
and I help out around here
as the community liaison

25:51.070 --> 25:54.062
between Charley
and the Black Farmers
Collective.

25:54.110 --> 25:56.066
So, you are the one

25:56.110 --> 25:58.590
who is helping Charley
expand her business.

25:58.640 --> 26:02.371
[laughs]
Well, he's the reason
I have any business.

26:02.430 --> 26:05.206
Well, Mr. Newell,
that is extreme high praise

26:05.250 --> 26:06.854
coming from my daughter.

26:06.910 --> 26:09.606
So, I need to get
to know you better.

26:10.690 --> 26:11.770
Okay.

26:17.610 --> 26:19.749
[ chatter ]

26:31.590 --> 26:33.319
Nova:
I hoped for
a larger turnout.

26:33.370 --> 26:37.409
Well, it ain't hard
for fear to turn
into distrust.

26:37.460 --> 26:39.416
I've been
in the community,
Chantal.

26:39.460 --> 26:42.634
When a lot of other people
moved on, I stayed.

26:42.680 --> 26:44.329
I've been here.

26:48.120 --> 26:49.815
[ boy coughing ]

26:49.860 --> 26:51.908
Nova:
And now I'll--
I'll take questions.

26:51.950 --> 26:54.293
[ people murmuring ]

26:54.350 --> 26:55.567
Y
es, ma'am?

26:55.610 --> 26:57.999
Are there any cases
down here?

26:58.050 --> 27:00.473
There are about
20 cases confirmed
in New Orleans today.

27:00.530 --> 27:01.610
That's all?

27:01.660 --> 27:03.651
Ms. Nova,
why did you write

27:03.700 --> 27:06.225
in the paper
that our neighborhood

27:06.270 --> 27:07.965
is a breeding ground
for Zika?

27:08.010 --> 27:10.797
You're right,
it's not a lot.

27:10.840 --> 27:13.308
First, I wrote that
because I believe it.

27:13.370 --> 27:16.009
Second, the conditions here
make it a real possibility.

27:16.060 --> 27:19.678
Woman:
It's possible I'll hit
the lottery later on today,

27:19.720 --> 27:21.847
but that don't mean
I should go off

27:21.900 --> 27:23.800
telling folks
it's gonna happen.

27:23.850 --> 27:26.023
[ crowd murmuring ]

27:31.250 --> 27:32.729
I mean,
she blows into town

27:32.780 --> 27:34.771
months after I had
to bury my father--

27:34.820 --> 27:36.731
her ex-husband--
and-- and now,

27:36.780 --> 27:38.213
she just wants
instant access

27:38.260 --> 27:39.693
into everything
going on in my life.

27:39.740 --> 27:40.957
Well, I'm sure
she means well.

27:41.000 --> 27:42.524
Well, then she should've
been here,

27:42.570 --> 27:43.730
but she sends flowers.

27:43.790 --> 27:46.350
She writes the most
beautiful postcards

27:46.400 --> 27:48.356
from _all
of the exotic places
she visits

27:48.400 --> 27:49.571
- and-- and--
- Sounds kind of nice.

27:49.620 --> 27:51.668
No, she's good
on the page,

27:51.710 --> 27:52.927
less so in person.

27:52.970 --> 27:54.528
[ phone rings ]

27:54.580 --> 27:56.969
[ sighs ]

27:57.020 --> 27:58.624
Hey, Davis.

28:01.590 --> 28:04.320
Okay.

28:04.370 --> 28:06.418
I'll-- I'll be
right there.

28:06.460 --> 28:09.509
Have you been feeling
achy at all, Miles?

28:09.550 --> 28:12.018
- No, sir.
- Woman: Well, I thought
I heard something

28:12.080 --> 28:13.889
about the Zika
messing with the eyes.

28:13.950 --> 28:15.724
Yes, it can cause
conjunctivitis.

28:15.780 --> 28:17.429
That's, uh, pink eye.

28:17.470 --> 28:18.687
- Woman: Oh.
- Okay.

28:18.740 --> 28:22.346
Look straight ahead.
Coming in close.

28:22.390 --> 28:25.609
All right, other side,
straight ahead.

28:25.660 --> 28:28.390
- Looks normal.
-[laughs]

28:28.440 --> 28:31.523
I mean, you know,
he wants to go out and play,
but after that article,

28:31.570 --> 28:34.266
_ there's all
this standing water
outside of my apartment.

28:34.320 --> 28:36.220
I mean, I'm just
a nervous wreck.

28:36.270 --> 28:37.669
I understand
why that article
made you worry,

28:37.710 --> 28:40.497
but the good news
for Miles is

28:40.540 --> 28:42.758
there's no reason
to believe--

28:42.800 --> 28:46.099
head up--
that these are
anything more

28:46.150 --> 28:48.198
than _normal
moquIto bites.

28:48.240 --> 28:49.286
Okay, good.

28:49.330 --> 28:50.501
And Zika's preventable,

28:50.550 --> 28:53.155
so let Miles
go outside and play.

28:53.200 --> 28:55.202
Just make sure
he has on repellent.

28:55.250 --> 28:56.899
- Okay.
- All right?

28:56.950 --> 28:58.770
You guys
are good to go.

29:01.820 --> 29:03.685
- Thanks again.
- You are most welcome.

29:03.740 --> 29:06.038
Oh, oh, here we go.

29:06.090 --> 29:07.694
- [ both imitating explosion ]
-[laughs]

29:07.740 --> 29:09.560
Thank you.
Come on, now.

29:15.100 --> 29:17.261
[ blows ]

29:17.320 --> 29:18.617
- Can you fix it?
- Yeah.

29:18.660 --> 29:20.833
- [ air hissing ]
- [ door opens ]

29:20.880 --> 29:23.792
- Ralph Angel:
What up, y'all?
- Violet: Oh, I know

29:23.840 --> 29:25.626
- you're here for something.
- [ door closes ]

29:25.670 --> 29:27.535
Don't be like that,
Aunt Vi.

29:27.590 --> 29:29.194
- Yeah, I suspect...
- What up, Wood?

29:29.240 --> 29:31.288
...there's some babysitting
always coming up.

29:31.330 --> 29:34.197
Y'all know how much
we love baby Blue...

29:34.250 --> 29:35.501
- [ Holleood chuckles ]
- ...but I just can't--

29:35.550 --> 29:38.417
It's... not why we came.

29:42.910 --> 29:44.810
We getting married.

29:44.870 --> 29:48.556
-[laughs]
Ah, congratulations, man!
- [ grunts ]

29:48.610 --> 29:50.692
- [ grunts ]
- I appreciate that, Wood.

29:50.740 --> 29:52.731
Yes. God knows we need
some good news around here, so.

29:52.790 --> 29:55.042
- Darla: Thank you,
Holleood.
- Mwah!

29:57.530 --> 29:58.838
Aunt Vi...

30:00.400 --> 30:02.095
Marriage is forever,
y'all.

30:04.320 --> 30:05.878
Aunt Vi, we grown.

30:05.930 --> 30:09.366
I've been working hard
running the farm,

30:09.410 --> 30:11.458
about to bring in
the first harvest.

30:11.500 --> 30:14.196
I've been sober
for two years.

30:16.330 --> 30:18.116
I know.

30:18.160 --> 30:21.505
- And we are
very proud of you.
- [ chuckles ]

30:21.550 --> 30:23.939
[laughs]

30:23.990 --> 30:26.242
But that's just it,
y'all been so good

30:26.300 --> 30:27.813
at taking baby steps,

30:27.860 --> 30:30.169
you sure you want
to go all in right now?

30:30.210 --> 30:32.349
Sometimes you gotta
just bet on yourself.

30:34.520 --> 30:37.171
- I know that's right.
- [ chuckles ]

30:37.220 --> 30:39.871
I'm happy.
[laughs]

30:39.920 --> 30:42.616
- Oh, congratulations.
- Thank you.

30:42.660 --> 30:44.218
[laughs]

30:44.270 --> 30:47.319
And I can't wait
to meet your folks, Darla.

30:49.150 --> 30:51.232
I just, you know,
wanted to make sure

30:51.280 --> 30:53.919
you were sure,
save you any hardships.

30:53.980 --> 30:55.754
I get it.

30:55.810 --> 30:59.234
Whatever comes our way,
we'll face it together.

30:59.290 --> 31:01.542
- That's good, baby.
- That's right, that's right.

31:01.590 --> 31:03.672
- Oh, that's good.
- You're getting married, boy.

31:03.730 --> 31:05.948
[ all laughing ]

31:18.700 --> 31:20.042
We have _to do
something.

31:20.090 --> 31:22.046
- Davis, you hear me?
- Mom.

31:22.090 --> 31:23.910
We have to call
our attorney now.

31:23.960 --> 31:26.656
- I don't want all of that.
- Micah, we have to fight.

31:28.320 --> 31:30.265
Mom, I really want
to put this behind me.

31:30.320 --> 31:32.663
Davis, tell him.
We have the resources,
we have the contacts.

31:32.710 --> 31:35.099
- Charley, you heard Micah.
- Why are you both okay
with this?

31:35.150 --> 31:37.015
Charley, it's not okay!

31:38.940 --> 31:40.749
It's not okay.

31:40.810 --> 31:42.766
All right?
Nobody's saying that.

31:45.160 --> 31:47.378
I'm sorry,
I'm sorry.

31:50.560 --> 31:52.812
I'm so sorry,
I'm so sorry.

31:54.650 --> 31:56.163
Micah.

31:58.960 --> 32:00.689
[crying ]

32:10.790 --> 32:12.519
Hollywood:
Yeah, so I told Vi

32:12.580 --> 32:15.959
that we would just come here
and pick her up from here.

32:16.020 --> 32:18.181
And we'll just
figure it out after that.

32:18.240 --> 32:20.310
But it don't look
like nobody here.

32:20.370 --> 32:22.406
- Blue: Surprise!
- All: Surprise!

32:22.460 --> 32:23.802
- [ music playing ]
- [ all cheering ]

32:23.850 --> 32:25.192
Nova:
You can blame Aunt Vi.

32:25.240 --> 32:27.231
She got us all to come.
Congratulations.

32:27.290 --> 32:29.155
Thank you.

